{"id": "1519277477153738822", "channel_id": "1504798331593818263", "author_id": "1060975277531992145", "author_name": "arandomflamev2", "content": "note: Pcaro is a shorter way to type propagation caro\nThe current consensus about Pcaro is that compared to other realm variations is just worse from multiple points of view:\n-every character that has embryo generation is by default worse in Pcaro since they give only half of the values that they had in normal caro\n-first devour a powerful tool that was helped caro sustain at low hp, the intended way to play caro carries, is gone\n-Bottomless scar is a bigger problem in Pcaro, since the new way to sustain with crimson furnace is a really fast way to hit it\n-Exalt buffs are nice but not everyone does something with it. Characters like faint, helot, Aigis get nothing from it.\n-the realm and saya are just designed around eachother. Right now its \"fine\" since only she brings it but the realm can very easily feel worse when a new unit with Pcaro releases and it doesn't help as much as saya does. Some aspects of Pcaro are also really weird and make sense only when taking saya into consideration. +10% max hp cus saya's con stats are worse, corrosion on furnace doesn't really make sense.\nIf future caro units need to be released with a realm variantion, it needs to be less limiting and less anti-synergistic with older caro units, while the current exalt enhancement numbers can be reduced to make it more balanced.", "timestamp": "2026-06-24T09:46:17.364000+00:00", "type": 19, "thread_id": "1504798331593818263", "mentions": ["1437487264023318668"], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "reply_to": "1519272439933173761"}
{"id": "1519279619289776138", "channel_id": "1504798331593818263", "author_id": "1060975277531992145", "author_name": "arandomflamev2", "content": "for short: Very hostile to previous caro units, and is seen as a straight up downgrade except for very few specific teams compared to divine aequor and singularity ultra who are seen as either sidegrades or just buffs", "timestamp": "2026-06-24T09:54:48.089000+00:00", "thread_id": "1504798331593818263"}
